        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tts): sanitize summarized speech text",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #90364.\n\nTTS summarization now sanitizes summary-model output before returning text for speech:\n\n- strips assistant/control scaffolding, echoed summary prompt instructions, narrow leading prompt preambles, exact echoed source blocks, and standalone or same-line echoed `<text_to_summarize>` prompt blocks\n- preserves legitimate first-person summaries, user-summary prose, inline prompt-tag mentions, and quoted/parenthesized sentence endings before stripped prompt echoes\n- keeps cleanup in `summarizeText`, before auto-TTS assigns `summary.summary` to audio text\n\nFinal surface after trimming: 2 files, +194/-56.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`src/tts/tts-core.ts` joined `TextContent` blocks from `completeSimple` and returned the raw string as `summary.summary`. Auto-TTS then used that value directly as `textForAudio`, so reasoning tags, control tokens, prompt echo, or echoed source text could be spoken.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Long-response TTS summaries no longer pass hidden reasoning/control scaffolding, echoed prompt text, exact echoed source prompt blocks, standalone or same-line prompt-block echoes, quoted/parenthesized same-line prompt echoes, or control tokens through to the audio text candidate. Regression cases also cover preserving first-person `key points` prose, preserving inline `<text_to_summarize>` mentions, and stripping bare `The user asked me to summarize.` prompt echoes.\n\nReal environment tested: Dedicated local macOS OpenClaw source checkout on branch `codex/fix-tts-summary-sanitization` at commit `1ea11d78a6`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm exec tsx /private/tmp/openclaw-tts-summary-proof.ts`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```console\nOpenClaw TTS summary proof\nsanitizedSummary=\"Concise audible summary.\"\nsanitizedOutputLength=24\ntargetLength=120\nleakedForbiddenTokens=none\nfirstPersonSummary=\"I need to keep the key points from today's review. The release moves to Friday.\"\nfirstPersonPreserved=yes\ninlineTagSummary=\"The docs mention `<text_to_summarize>` as a literal prompt marker. The release moves to Friday.\"\ninlineTagPreserved=yes\njoinedPromptSummary=\"Concise audible summary.\"\nsameLinePromptSummary=\"Concise audible summary.\"\nquotedPromptSummary=\"\\\"Deploy Friday.\\\"\"\nparenthesizedPromptSummary=\"(Deploy Friday.)\"\nbareUserPromptSummary=\"Deployment was delayed until Friday.\"\naudioText=Concise audible summary.\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The production `summarizeText` cleanup path returned only `Concise audible summary.` for scaffolded summary-model output, preserved the first-person and inline-tag summaries, stripped joined and same-line prompt-block echoes, preserved quoted/parenthesized audible sentence endings while stripping their prompt echoes, and stripped the bare user-summary prompt echo.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Microsoft/MiniMax audio playback was not run because provider credentials and audio playback setup were not available in this local checkout.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tts/tts-core.test.ts packages/speech-core/src/tts.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec tsx /private/tmp/openclaw-tts-summary-proof.ts`\n\nFocused verification passed: 2 Vitest files / 44 tests, plus the production-path local proof script output above.",
